News reports have confirmed that Patricia de Lille has resigned from her position as leader of the DA in the Western Cape.Many have expressed shock as the news of her resignation started spreading on social media on Monday morning. It is reported that De Lille wrote a letter of resignation DA leader Mmusi Maimane informing him of her decision.Social media went buzzing as many reject reasons provided by De Lille for her resignation. Her reason as stated on her letter is that she wants to focus on her position as the mayor of the City of Cape Town. comments